The former refugee transit camp is being converted into an IDP camp and at the same time expanded.  All tents are being replaced, significant earthworks are required in new areas but also improvements for road ways, plots and drainage in old areas.  There are currently IDPs on the site and this presents a challenge for construction activities.
Main Priority: Most services are 'emergency' by nature for example the water supply is trucked, these services are there for the current small IDP population and will be switched to more sustainable models before the camp is fully populated.  Main priority is to complete the construction works to allow the full camp to be operational.
Active Services: Potable Water, Sanitation facilities, Core Relief Item Distribution, Health Facilities
